column1: # Celestial coordinates, proper motions, magnitudes and the masses of the possible members of Alpha Persi as found by this study,
# sorted by right ascension from PPMXL.
# Stellar masses are derived from the J magnitudes using a PARSEC isochorne. In the last column, 'D' and 'L' letters correspond to
# Deacon & Hambly (2004) and Lodieu et al. (2012) respectively and show whether the members have also been designated by these studies.
# column 12: Whether the star is also found in Deacon, N. R., Hambly, N. C., 2004, A&A, 416, 125 or
# in Lodieu, N., Deacon, N. R., Hambly, N. C., Boudreault, S., 2012, MNRAS, 426, 3403L
